    description: "The Bachelor of Social Science degree (BSocSc) studies how human societies are organised, the social forces, institutions and ideologies that shape society, and the factors that influence the wellbeing of individuals, families, communities, and countries. The scope of the course includes key topics like class, gender, religion and race. Students develop the ability to analyse contemporary social issues and policy responses in areas such as poverty and social exclusion, drug use, criminal justice, housing, migration, ethnicity, disability, ageing, and gender. A key focus is on addressing inequa",
