    fullSummary: "Power up your future: Dive into the world of computing and software, MU graduates are highly sought after by employers: 83% of 2023 mastering everything from programming and problem-solving to cuttingedge technologies and mathematical principles. Shape your own learning journey: With a wide range of cuttingedge modules, you can dive into the most exciting and relevant areas of Computer Science, from gaining vital software engineering skills, networking, cryptography to artificial intelligence and beyond. Get hands-on from day one! You'll develop practical programming skills and advanced problem-solving techniques in our state-of-the-art Eolas building—Maynooth’s €20M ICT hub with top-tier labs and facilities. Explore beyond Computer Science: In first year, you’ll have the chance to study another Arts Subject or Critical Skills with Computer Science and Mathematics, allowing you to broaden your knowledge and discover new interests. Real-world industry experience: A six-month placement in third year gives you the chance to work in industry, gain professional experience, and build career connections—many students secure job offers before completing their placement! Collaborate on exciting projects: Throughout the course you will work on individual and team projects. In third year, you’ll work as part of a team to solve real-world challenges in Computer Science, developing teamwork, communication, and technical skills. A pathway into software engineering: If you start in MH101 Arts, you can transfer to second year MH601 CSA (Computer Science and Software Engineering. See page 38. Supportive student-centred approach: Enjoy a friendly and inclusive learning environment, with accessible academic staff, practical support, and a dedicated Computer Science Centre. A thriving Computer Science community: Maynooth University’s Computer Science Centre (CSC) supports students at all levels—whether you need extra help with coursework or want to take on advanced challenges. With competitions, events, and social activities throughout the year, it’s a great way to connect, collaborate, and be part of a dynamic CS community. From second year, students can volunteer as tutors within the CSC, enhancing teaching and communication skills. graduates were in employment or full-time education in the 6 months after graduation, including in companies. Tech skills that open endless doors: Computing, programming, and software development are in high demand across industries. From AI and medical imaging to game development, multimedia systems, and cybersecurity, the possibilities are endless! Not just for tech careers: Computer Science graduates are highly valued in finance, business, healthcare, automotive, aeronautics, and more. The broad range of first-year subjects ensures you develop versatile skills for a variety of career paths. Shape the future in education: With Computer Science now a secondlevel teaching subject, this degree can also lead to a rewarding career in education, inspiring the next generation of tech innovators. Why Choose/Study MH601 This programme offers a strong foundation in computing, combined with practical experience, industry connections, and flexible study options. Whether you are interested in software development, artificial intelligence, multimedia, web development, or interdisciplinary applications, MH601 provides the skills and opportunities to prepare you for a successful career.",
